{
  "texts": [
    "the Cartesian product is pinched by retracting ∂Σ × I ≃ ∂Σ so that ∂(Σ × I) = Σ ∪ Σ).",
    "Given [x] ∈ A(Σ; b) and [y] ∈ A(Σ; b ′) we put ([x], [y]) A(Σ):= δ b b ′ Z Σ×I (x ∪ y),where x ∪ y is the string diagram on ∂(Σ × I) consisting of string diagram x on Σ and string diagram y on Σ.",
    "This yields a well-defined inner product on A(Σ) which we will call the TQFT inner product.It is straightforward to verify that the Tube actions on the various boundary components of Σ are *-actions w.r.t.",
    "the TQFT inner product.",
    "This gives A(Σ) the structure of a unitary A(∂Σ)-module."
  ]
}